comments: James (LAL) and Caruso (CHI) engage and disengage with one another as they each attempt to obtain post position.
After the pass is deflected, Ball (CHI) makes clean contact with the ball and bats it away from Ariza (LAL) before incidental contact occurs with Ariza's front.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Ariza (LAL) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Green (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Ariza's (LAL) view and gives Ariza a step of distance to avoid the contact, which Green absorbs.
Westbrook (LAL) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
James (LAL) engages and disengages with Ball (CHI) off-ball.
James (LAL) brushes DeRozan's (CHI) side and marginal contact occurs before James cleanly blocks the driving shot attempt. The block occurs prior to the ball making contact with the backboard.
DeRozan's (CHI) right leg is slightly extended backward as he is airborne and marginal contact occurs with James' (LAL) lower half as James contests the shot attempt.
Vucevic (CHI) brings his left arm toward Ariza's (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs to Ariza's front as the rebound falls toward the corner.
There is not clear and conclusive video evidence determining if Ball's (CHI) left foot steps out of bounds after he receives the pass.
Anthony (LAL) brings his hands toward Green's (CHI) front and marginal contact occurs as Green is airborne retrieving the rebound.
James (LAL) closes out the jump shot attempt and any marginal contact that occurs is the result of DeRozan (CHI) slightly extending his right leg forward during the follow-through.

James' (LAL) right arm is extended forward following the shot contest and marginal contact occurs with DeRozan's (CHI) head after DeRozan returns to the floor. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Green (CHI) and James (LAL) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Vucevic (CHI) turns alongside Westbrook's (LAL) path and marginal body contact occurs as Westbrook fades away during the driving shot attempt.
Anthony (LAL) and Vucevic (CHI) engage and disengage with one another as Vucevic moves to set the pick.
Rondo (LAL) closes out the jump shot attempt and marginal body contact occurs as DeRozan (CHI) turns with his right leg slightly extended during the follow-through.
Ball (CHI) cleanly back-taps the rebound before incidental arm contact occurs with Ariza (LAL).
Rondo (LAL) commits a take foul on DeRozan (CHI).
James' (LAL) right arm slightly extends outward as he firms up in his screening position and he absorbs the contact made with Vucevic (CHI).
James (LAL) sets the pick on Ball (CHI) and, after absorbing the initial contact, marginal contact occurs with Ball's side as James releases away to roll.
Vucevic (CHI) legally contests Anthony's (LAL) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Westbrook (LAL) engages and disengages with Green (CHI) as he crashes to back-tap the ball during rebounding.
DeRozan (CHI) legally contests Ellington's (LAL) jump shot attempt.
James (LAL) commits a take foul on Ball (CHI).
